{"title":"Lotus Unveils 9.8kg e-Road Bike w/ 300g Motor","link":"https://bikerumor.com/lotus-unveils-9-8kg-e-road-bike-w-300g-motor/","date":1698854837000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3.jpg\" alt=\"rider standing next to lotus type 136 e-road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3.jpg 1920w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-3-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></p>\n<p>Lotus (yes, that Lotus) has just released the lightest-ever road e-bike, the Type 136, with an ultralight HPS motor and battery system that’s just 1,200g all-in. Combined with a lightweight carbon frame, the complete bike is just 9.8kg (21.61lb). And it’ll run you about $2,600 per kilo.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"lotus type 136 e-road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-5.jpg 1920w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame’s design is a nod to the Olympic track-winning Lotus 108 that raced at the 1998 Barcelona games and the more recent <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-hope-x-lotus-hb-t-next-gen-track-bike/\">Hope/Lotus collaboration</a> for Sir Chris Hoy. Which means it’s more than light, it’s also aerodynamic.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4.jpg\"><img width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4.jpg\" alt=\"handlebar detail on lotus type 136 e-road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4.jpg 1920w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-4-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Type 136 was designed by Lotus designer and aerodynamicist Richard Hill, getting the same V-shaped handlebars, wing-shaped fork, and vaulted chainstays as the track latest track bikes. No split seatpost though, but this one does get an integrated tail light flowing out of the saddle clamp area.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2.jpg\"><img width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2.jpg\" alt=\"battery detail on lotus type 136 e-road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2.jpg 1920w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-2-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The HPS (High Performance Systems) Watt Assist Pro motor is minuscule, borrowing tech designed for the Mars rover. As such, it’s light (just 300g) and compact, fitting in a standard-looking bottom bracket shell. It only puts out 136 watts, so it’s truly there to assist not dominate. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lotus suggests it doesn’t create much if any drag when it’s not assisting, either. Which is handy, because the battery is disguised as a water bottle – just disconnect it and ride like normal. Fully charged they say it’s good for about three hours of riding.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1.jpg\"><img width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1.jpg\" alt=\"lotus type 136 e-road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1.jpg 1920w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/lotus-type-136-carbon-e-road-bike-1-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This launch edition bike costs £20,000 (€25,000) and is limited to 136 units, all signed and numbered. They’re painted in classic Lotus racing livery and spec’d with <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-campagnolo-super-record-wireless-road-bike-groupset/\">Campagnolo Super Record Wireless</a>. A standard edition will follow in early 2024 with bikes from £15,199 to £16,999 (€17,950 to €19,950) with SRAM drivetrains.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.lotuscars.com/en-GB/type-136\" target=\"_blank\">LotusCars.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/lotus-unveils-9-8kg-e-road-bike-w-300g-motor/\">Lotus Unveils 9.8kg e-Road Bike w/ 300g Motor</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a02bad8e09241387de21046f3f4d5b4839ecce2a44d5a810a452a2125382f228","category":"Cycling"}